Job Description:
We are seeking a dedicated and knowledgeable ACMV (Air-Conditioning and Mechanical Ventilation) Engineer. The successful candidate will be responsible for the design, coordination, installation, testing, commission, and maintenance of ACMV systems in line with project specifications, codes, and industry best practices.

Key Responsibilities:
• Design and develop ACMV systems including load calculations, equipment selection, and layout planning;
• Review and coordinate ACMV system drawings (schematic, single-line, shop drawings) with other disciplines;
• Manage works, design schedule of mechanical services based on the overall schedule of the project;
• Prepare technical submissions, equipment / material specifications, and method statements;
• Authorship supervision of ACMV installation work on-site to ensure compliance with design and quality standards;
• Liaise with other consultants, sub-consultants, contractors to resolve technical and coordination issues;
• Witness the testing & commissioning (T&C) of ACMV systems and ensure all performance parameters are met;
• Prepare site Authorship reports, technical issues, T&C results, and as-built documentation;
• Support maintenance and troubleshooting activities for completed ACMV systems (if applicable);
• Ensure all the design work complies with relevant codes, safety standards, and environmental regulations;
• Report to Team Leader and M&E Manager.

Job Requirements:
• Education: Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical Engineering, Building Services, or related field.
• Experience: Minimum 3-4 years of experience in ACMV design consultancy roles.
• Technical Competencies:
• High proficiency in English is an ADVANTAGE;
• Familiar with local codes & standards and statutory requirements. Having experiences working with international codes & standards is a strong plus;
• Proficient in AutoCAD, Revit, and other necessary software.
Soft Skills:
• Strong problem-solving, communication, and coordination skills;
• Able to work independently and as part of a multi-disciplinary team.

Job Description:
1. Manage bank’s securities investment portfolio including: Treasury bonds, Government underwriting bonds, FI Bonds and CDs (only HTM and AFS, no trading).
2. Work with market for update bond/CD offers and complete investment deals, both primary and secondary market: Review OC, T&C, contracts, documents; Work with Back Office for system booking and settlement.
3. Make application, proposal for investment deals for FI customers: Analyze FI’s financial statements, financial ratios, business information, and market update;
4. Market analysis and being the contact point and work with other financial institutions to expand relationship and business opportunities;
Bond/CD Issuance
1. Prepare for issuance plan and all issuance documents (OC, Terms & Conditions, Agreements,…), work with all internal and external parties to finish issuance.
2. Work with interbank and market for pricing and market demand, finding investors;
3. Manage post-issuance for bond/CD, support back office for deal settlement and periodic information disclosure;
Reporting
Periodical internal reports (weekly, monthly securities evaluation), external report to SBV, VSDC, HNX upon request.

Job Requirements:
• Experienced dealer in securities investment, securities evaluation (Gov-bond, Financial Institutions Bond/CD);
• Experienced in securities issuance (Bond/CD), updated laws and regulations (Decree 65, Circular 76, bond registration at VSDC, bond transaction at HNX);
• Work carefully, teamwork & responsibility, supporting for other desks of dealing room if needed;
• Good computer skills (Excel, PowerPoint), formulas for bond evaluation.
• Good written/spoken English.

